quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,16,"Did He take daughters (for Himself) from what He creates, and He chose sons for you"
  43,17,"And when one of them is given good news of what he assigns to the beneficent, his face turns dark (and shameful) while he holds back his anger"
  43,18,"Or (do they assign to God) someone who is raised in luxury, and who is unclear in the debate"
  43,19,"And they made the angels, those who are servants of the beneficent, females! Did they witness their creation? Their testimony is going to be written down and they will be questioned"
  43,20,"And they said: if the beneficent wanted, we would not have served them. They have no knowledge of that, they only guess"
  43,21,"Or did We give them a book before it, which they are adhering to it"
  43,22,"No, but they said: we found our fathers on a course, and we are guided by their footsteps"
  43,23,"And the same way, We did not send any town anyone as a warner before you, unless its rich (and wealthy) said: we found our fathers on a course, and we are following their footsteps"
  43,24,"He (the warner) said: even if I have brought you a better guidance than what you found your fathers upon it? They said: we disbelieve in what you were sent with it"
  43,25,"Then We took revenge from them, so see what the end of those who denied was"